Thanks a lot Bubanee!! This is a good album. It has that "live in the studio" sound, which to my aging ears sounds much better than the  over-produced overdubbed recordings of today.
I especially like the versions of "Hear My Train a Comin", and "Sunshine of your love". Highly recommended for any Hendrix fan!

Oh, and I almost forgot about the 12 minute slow ... blues .... version of "Red House". Sure, there are many Hendrix recordings of Red House out there; but he never played the same notes twice you know! I am always happy to hear one more Hendrix performance of Red House.
